  "prompt": "Which is the best app to track markets?",
  "response": "The best app to track markets can vary depending on individual needs and preferences, but here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Bloomberg**: Offers comprehensive market data, news, and analysis. It's highly regarded for its detailed information and professional-grade tools.\n\n2. **Yahoo Finance**: A user-friendly app with extensive market data, news, and personalized portfolio tracking. Good for both beginners and experienced investors.\n\n3. **CNBC**: Provides real-time market data, breaking news, and expert analysis. Also includes live TV streaming for financial news.\n\n4. **TradingView**: Known for its advanced charting tools and social community features. Great for technical analysis and connecting with other traders.\n\n5. **MarketWatch**: Delivers market news, stock data, and portfolio tracking. Offers a range of articles and financial analysis.\n\n6. **Robinhood**: While primarily a trading app, Robinhood offers real-time market data, news, and analysis. It\u2019s particularly popular among younger investors.\n\n7. **Investing.com**: Comprehensive app with real-time data, news, analysis, and financial tools. Covers global markets extensively.\n\nUltimately, the best app depends on your specific needs, such as the level of detail you require, whether you need real-time data, or if you prefer a more community-oriented platform.",
